article.description: UC Davis 80, Notre Dame de Namur 53
article.headline: UC Davis 80, Notre Dame de Namur 53
article.linkText: UC Davis 80, Notre Dame de Namur 53
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Eddie Miller scored 15 points and UC Davis hit a school record 15 3-pointers in an 80-53 victory over Notre Dame de Namur Saturday night. Tyler Les added 12 points, all on 3s, and Joe Harden also scored 12 for the Aggies (4-5), who eclipsed the previous mark of nine 3s in a game in the first half, making 10. Arron Mollet scored 14 points to lead the Argonauts (0-5), a Division II team. UC Davis led 46-20 at the break. Notre Dame de Namur closed to within 50-37 with 14:20 to play, but the Aggies put together a 20-2 run for a 70-39 advantage with 7:16 remaining. UC Davis led by at least 27 the rest of the way.
